    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in vendor extension packing functions\n\n### Summary\nThe `vnf_pack_p4_p5_vendor_extension` and `vnf_nr_pack_p4_p5_vendor_extension` functions in the VNF module contained inverted logic for return value handling. When packing vendor extension messages, these functions would incorrectly return 0 (failure) when both push operations succeeded and 1 (success) when either operation failed.\n\nThis could lead to downstream issues where the system would incorrectly report failure when operations actually succeeded, potentially causing message transmission failures or incorrect error handling during the NFAPI P5 communication between VNF and PNF.\n\nThe issue was particularly problematic during high-load scenarios where vendor extension messages are frequently exchanged, as it could cause connection instability between the VNF and PNF entities.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Fixed inverted return logic in `vnf_pack_p4_p5_vendor_extension` function\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Fixed inverted return logic in `vnf_nr_pack_p4_p5_vendor_extension` function\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Added proper handling for both P5_VENDOR_EXT_REQ and P5_VENDOR_EXT_RSP message types\n- `nfapi/oai_integration/nfapi_vnf.c`: Improved code structure using switch statements for better readability\n\n"
}